# Widgets

    - Attributes
        - android:layout_width and android:layout_height
            match_parent (view will be as big as its parent)
            wrap_content (view will be as big as its contents require)
            0dp (fill remain space) // just in ConstraintLayout with constraint
        - android:orientation 
            for LinearLayout accept horizontal and vertical
        - android:id="@+id/true_button"
        - android:gravity="center"
            for LinearLayout set child widgets positions
        - android:layout_gravity="bottom|right" or android:layout_gravity="center_vertical|center_horizontal" or android:layout_gravity="center_horizontal"
            for FrameLayout's children set own positions by gravity (apply to children)

    - Widget Icon
        put .png or .jpg files in src/main/res/drawable (id generated automatic)
        make screen density by folders drawable-hdpi, drawable-mdpi, drawable-xhdpi, and drawable-xxhdpi
        use in widget by following codes
        - android:src="@drawable/arrow_right" 
            example use in button or imageView
        - android:drawableRight="@drawable/arrow_right" 
            example use in image button   

    - Listener 
        - Checkbox
            setOnCheckedChangeListener
        - EditText
            addTextChangedListener
        - Button (and other)
            setOnClickListener

    - Wiring Up Widgets
        private Button mTrueButton; (class level)
        mTrueButton = findViewById(R.id.true_button); (onCreate method level)



    

     
        
        
         